\begin_layout Section
Conclusion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this paper, new insights on the construction of a P-function are used
 to yield exponential stability with RISE-based controllers.
 As an outcome of this breakthrough, the inherent learning capability of
 RISE-based controllers is shown to yield exponential identification of
 disturbances/uncertainty, as compared to all previous asymptotic results.
 Future work could involve extension of the proposed stability analysis
 methodology for RISE-based error systems with sensor noise, and delays
 in input and state measurements.
\end_layout

