The function 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{sgn}\left(e(\cdot)\right)$
\end_inset

 is discontinuous only at time-instants where it changes sign, i.e., the set
 
\begin_inset Formula $\{t\in\mathcal{I}|\exists i\in\{1,2,\ldots,n\}\,\textrm{s.t.}\,e_{i}\left(t\right)=0\:\wedge\dot{e}_{i}(t)\neq0\}=\{t\in\mathcal{I}|\exists i\in\{1,2,\ldots,n\}\,\textrm{s.t.}\,e_{i}\left(t\right)=0\:\wedge r_{i}(t)-\alpha e_{i}(t)\neq0\}=T$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 has Lebesgue measure zero according to Lemma 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "lem:meas_zero"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{sgn}\left(e(\cdot)\right)$
\end_inset

 is continuous a.e., implying it is Riemann integrable 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
